subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: The reigning Olympic champion Jenn Suhr broke her own women’s world indoor pole vault record by clearing 5.03 meters (16 feet 6 inches) at the Golden Eagle Invitational meet in Brockport, N.Y. Suhr broke the mark she established in 2013.
